<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="title">About PastaAtlas</h1>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="title is-4">What is PastaAtlas?</h2>
      <p>
        PastaAtlas is a web application for uploading and browsing Factorio world maps captured by the
        <a href="https://mods.factorio.com/mod/mapshot">mapshot</a> mod.
        Upload a tile set directly from your browser and share it with others,
        or explore maps that the community has shared.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="title is-4">Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Upload mapshot output (tile images and metadata) directly from your browser</li>
        <li>Browse maps shared by the community</li>
        <li>Interactive viewer with pan, zoom, surface switching, generation history, train station overlay, and resource tag overlays</li>
        <li>Sign in with GitHub, Discord, or Steam</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="title is-4">Built with</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Ruby &middot; Hanami 2 &middot; Dry.rb &middot; ROM.rb &middot; PostgreSQL</li>
        <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> SolidJS &middot; Leaflet &middot; Bulma &middot; TypeScript</li>
        <li><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> AWS S3 &middot; CloudFront &middot; ECS Fargate</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="title is-4">Author</h2>
      <p>Built by <a href="https://github.com/sakuro">sakuro</a>.</p>
    </section>

